HMD Global recently unveiled the Nokia 8 Sirocco, Nokia 7 Plus, and second-gen Nokia 6 in South Africa. The company has now revealed the local prepaid pricing for the new devices, which will be sold through Cell C, MTN, Vodacom, and retailers. HMD’s new Nokia smartphones are part of the Android One programme, and will receive OS and security updates soon after they are released by Google. The South African pricing for the new devices is below. The Nokia 7 Plus and Nokia 6 will be available from 19 and 23 April respectively. The Nokia 8 Sirocco will be available from 7 May.